ann ecv wieght 1 -a 260718
  # a typo cannot conjure a series
  => exit 4: no annales series "wieght" at ecv — mint it with -c (§7.3)
ann nosuch 1 -a 260718
  # no such series, tree-wide
  => exit 4: no annales series named "nosuch" — mint it with -c (§7.3)
ann weight 1 -c
  # -c is refused on an inference form
  => exit 2: -c needs the home and the series both named; it is refused on an inference form (§7.3)
ann rm 999999 --series weight -y
  # no line at that key
  => exit 4: no line keyed 999999 in series "weight" at ecv (§7.2)
ann list -k task
  # a token this core does not own
  => exit 2: annales has no "task" token; it declares `log` (§7.1)
ann ecv weight    -a 260722
  # a blank reading value
  => exit 3: reading value 0 is blank; a value nobody can read is not a fact (§8.6)
ann ecv weight 1 -a 260718
  # an overwrite, piped, without -y
  => exit 5: a pending add awaiting review
ann ecv 1 -a 260718
  # two series at the node: ambiguous
  => exit 2: ecv holds more than one annales series: places, weight — name one (§7.3)
ann ecv weight 1 -a sometime
  # a malformed --at
  => exit 2: -a takes YYMMDD, YYMMDDThhmm, or hhmm; got "sometime" (§7.3)
ann ecv weight 1 -a 260723 -r office
  # a malformed reference
  => exit 2: reference "office" is not `core:slug`
